### Scope boundaries (HARD rules)

- `laravel-developer` touches ONLY `backend/` — never `frontend/`
- `nextjs-developer` touches ONLY `frontend/` — never `backend/`
- `prototype-builder` touches ONLY `prototypes/` — never `backend/` or `frontend/`
- `postgres-architect` touches ONLY `backend/database/migrations/` and DB-related service files
- READ-ONLY agents (no Write/Edit): `repo-researcher`, `code-reviewer`, `security-auditor`, `architect-reviewer`, `performance-reviewer`, `dependency-reviewer`, `db-reviewer`, `api-contract-reviewer`, `ui-polish-reviewer`, `accessibility-reviewer`, `laravel-architect`, `nextjs-architect`, all researchers, all designers except prototype-builder

### Common workflows

**New feature (full-stack):**
1. `evolve:_product:systems-analyst` → requirements contract via `evolve:requirements-intake`
2. `evolve:_core:repo-researcher` → map existing code
3. `evolve:_product:product-manager` → PRD if user-facing (via `evolve:prd`)
4. `evolve:brainstorming` if complexity ≥7
5. `evolve:_design:creative-director` + `evolve:_design:prototype-builder` if UI feature → `evolve:prototype`
6. `evolve:writing-plans` → phased plan
7. `evolve:stacks/laravel:laravel-developer` → backend
8. `evolve:stacks/nextjs:nextjs-developer` → frontend
9. `evolve:_design:ui-polish-reviewer` → drift check
10. `evolve:_core:code-reviewer` → review
11. `evolve:_core:quality-gate-reviewer` → final ≥9 gate

**Bug fix:**
1. `evolve:_core:root-cause-debugger` via `evolve:systematic-debugging`
2. `evolve:tdd` regression test
3. `evolve:_core:code-reviewer`
4. `evolve:_core:quality-gate-reviewer`

**Brand reset / new product:**
1. `evolve:_design:creative-director` → direction
2. `evolve:_design:prototype-builder` → materialize via `evolve:brandbook` skill in `prototypes/_brandbook/`
3. `evolve:_design:copywriter` + `evolve:_design:accessibility-reviewer` review
4. User approval → brandbook becomes source-of-truth for all subsequent `evolve:prototype` invocations

### Mandatory subagent instructions

Every subagent prompt MUST include:

> ANTI-HALLUCINATION: Do not invent files, commands, or contracts that don't exist. Verify every claim with grep/read before reporting.
> CONFIDENCE-DISCIPLINE: Score your output via `evolve:confidence-scoring` before claiming done. <9 means not done unless `/evolve-override` was issued with reason.
> ZERO DEAD CODE: Every function/struct/variant/method you create MUST have at least one LIVE call site.

## Verification expectations

- `cd backend && ./vendor/bin/pest` — Pest tests (REQUIRED)
- `cd backend && ./vendor/bin/pint` — code style (REQUIRED, 0 changes)
- `cd backend && ./vendor/bin/phpstan analyse` — static analysis (REQUIRED, level max)
- `cd frontend && npm run typecheck` — TypeScript (REQUIRED)
- `cd frontend && npm test` — Vitest (REQUIRED)
- `cd frontend && npm run lint` — ESLint (REQUIRED)
- `cd frontend && npm run build` — Next.js build (REQUIRED before merge)
- `npm audit && composer audit` — security (REQUIRED before merge)

## Auto-evolve triggers

The main agent MUST suggest `/evolve <phase>` to the user when:

1. `.claude/agents/` empty or no routing table → `/evolve-genesis`
2. New module/command/service created → `/evolve-adapt`
3. New major dependency → `/evolve-adapt`
4. Agent failed due to stale context → `/evolve-audit`
5. >10 files changed in session → `/evolve-audit`
6. Oldest `last-verified` >30 days → `/evolve-audit + /evolve-strengthen`
7. New rule file in `.claude/rules/` → `evolve:_meta:rules-curator` review
8. Override-rate >5% over last 100 entries → `/evolve-audit`

